main event: A report of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) observed in Galveston, Indiana on June 6, 1964.
interesting points: The objects were observed at different times and locations, including south and east of the city.
The objects were at various altitudes, ranging from 55 degrees to 4 degrees above the horizon.
The objects were moving in different directions, including southeast and northeast.
The report indicates that the objects were initially stationary, then moved, and then a second object appeared from the north and approached the first object.
The report states that the objects could not be identified and that all possible explanations, including Apollo vehicles, were exhausted.
